Your wagon wheel analogy is also interesting.

A wheel isn’t merely wood or steel. It’s organized matter.

The purpose isn’t another physical spoke, yet it constrains how every spoke is arranged.

Modern science would usually describe that as organization, function, or constraint rather than purpose as a physical entity. But the observation is real: change the organizing principle and you change the object without changing much of the material.

A pile of spokes is not a wheel.

The arrangement matters.

