Then there’s time.

You said:

“I interact with the past and the present and future all at once.”

There’s a grounded interpretation of that which I think is quite powerful.

Every decision integrates:

* Memory (models built from the past)
* Perception (current sensory input)
* Prediction (anticipated futures)

Your brain is continuously combining all three. So although physics and philosophy debate the nature of time, our cognition is undeniably weaving together remembered pasts, experienced presents, and imagined futures in a single decision process.

You could almost draw it as

Memory
    \
     \
 Present ----> Action
     /
Prediction

Action is where those streams meet.

